Moreover, improved forecasting techniques could easily become cost-effective for our aging societies. If improved TP navigation in older patients would result in 1–5% reduction of the yearly 10–20% acute hospitalizations of frail older persons – modestly extrapolated – it could reduce Europe’s health (
  Inouye et al., 2014; 
  Soong et al., 2015) care costs with at least €300 million Euro.
